  "body": "As a user\r\nI want other users to display their identity ring in chat\r\nSo that I can make sure they are not impersonating someone else\r\n\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nIn the new designs, there's an identity ring around users pictures.\r\nThis should be served as an image in status-go, similarly how we display profile pictures.\r\nIdeally there's an endpoint that serves the profile picture already encircled in an identity ring, as a single picture.\r\n\r\n### Designs\r\n\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/h9wo4GipgZURbqqr1vShFN/Communities-for-Mobile?node-id=261%3A13411\r\n\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\nIt needs to be consistent with desktop so \r\n\r\n1) use the same color palette (tricky thing is that according to design it differs per theme, see https://github.com/status-im/StatusQ/blob/bb9f08155fd68a0e2f1a257ee2566099c86cecd0/src/StatusQ/Core/Theme/StatusDarkTheme.qml#L165 and https://github.com/status-im/StatusQ/blob/bb9f08155fd68a0e2f1a257ee2566099c86cecd0/src/StatusQ/Core/Theme/StatusLightTheme.qml#L163)\r\n2) use the same initalAngleRad and the direction of colors \r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/StatusQ/blob/master/src/StatusQ/Controls/StatusIdenticonRing.qml is the desktop implementation\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-go/blob/d0f4a94f7502ce37adf1f08065b07262b682c4bf/protocol/identity/colorhash/colorhash.go is the status-go implementation that defines how colorshash is constructed, but no rendering",
